[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libuv/libuv/issues/comments/259094112","html_url":"https://github.com/libuv/libuv/issues/1128#issuecomment-259094112","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libuv/libuv/issues/1128","id":259094112,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI1OTA5NDExMg==","user":{"login":"bnoordhuis","id":275871,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI3NTg3MQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/275871?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis","html_url":"https://github.com/bnoordhuis","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2016-11-08T09:58:16Z","updated_at":"2016-11-08T09:58:16Z","body":"TLS support was discussed at the summit in Amsterdam last September.  Our position is that we are unlikely to integrate TLS in libuv itself but we are open to hosting external contributions under the libuv umbrella in the https://github.com/libuv/libuv-extras repository.\n\nThe problem I see with TLS in libuv core is that we either say \"we only support openssl\" (or gnutls, or nss, or gskit, or mbedtls, or wolfssl, or...) or we write a leaky abstraction layer.\n\nIt's already difficult enough to paper over the differences between openssl, libressl and boringssl that I'm skeptical it would work for libraries without a shared heritage.\n\nlibcurl does it but libcurl ruthlessly trades features for interoperability and even then it's mostly about making other libraries look like openssl.\n\nThe bar for libuv should be higher: it's not interesting to me personally until it's a mostly drop-in replacement for the tls module in node.js.\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libuv/libuv/issues/comments/259094112/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"bnoordhuis","id":275871,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI3NTg3MQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/275871?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis","html_url":"https://github.com/bnoordhuis","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"id":851236628,"node_id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDg1MTIzNjYyOA==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libuv/libuv/issues/events/851236628","actor":{"login":"bnoordhuis","id":275871,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI3NTg3MQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/275871?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis","html_url":"https://github.com/bnoordhuis","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/followers","following_url":"https://api.git